"Besson U., De Ambrosis A., Mascheretti P.","Studying the physical basis of global warming: Thermal effects of the interaction between radiation and matter and greenhouse effect",2010,"European Journal of Physics","31","2",,"375","388",,,10.1088/0143-0807/31/2/015,"http://www.scopus.com/inward/record.url?eid=2-s2.0-77649218354&partnerID=40&md5=4f6dc588247279c0eaeb619ec7f45020","Department of Physics A Volta, University of Pavia, Via A Bassi 6, 27100 Pavia, Italy","Besson, U., Department of Physics A Volta, University of Pavia, Via A Bassi 6, 27100 Pavia, Italy; De Ambrosis, A., Department of Physics A Volta, University of Pavia, Via A Bassi 6, 27100 Pavia, Italy; Mascheretti, P., Department of Physics A Volta, University of Pavia, Via A Bassi 6, 27100 Pavia, Italy","We present a teaching module dealing with the thermal effects of interaction between radiation and matter, the infrared emission of bodies and the greenhouse effect devoted to university level and teacher education. The module stresses the dependence of the optical properties of materials (transparency, absorptivity and emissivity) on radiation frequency, as a result of interaction between matter and radiation. Multiple experiences are suggested to favour a progressive construction of knowledge on the physical aspects necessary to understand the greenhouse effect and global warming. Some results obtained with university students are briefly reported. © 2010 IOP Publishing Ltd.",,"Absorptivities; Infrared emissions; Optical properties of materials; Physical aspects; Radiation frequencies; Teacher education; Teaching module; University levels; University students; Carbon dioxide; Global warming; Greenhouses; Materials properties; Optical properties; Radiation effects; Teaching; Greenhouse effect",,,,,,"Besson, U., Borghi, L., De Ambrosis, A., Mascheretti, P., A three-dimensional approach and open source structure for the design and experimentation of teaching learning sequences: The case of friction (2009)